    <text id="B1264T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Cook reports on the County taxes assessed for 1866, including the levy for poor
                    relief. </p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. and
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/>Office <abbr expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst. Supt.</abbr>
                    Sub-<abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Captain R. S. Lacey<lb/>Superintendent Seventh <abbr
                            expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr><lb/>Lynchburg, Va.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-07-03">July 3d 1866</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to make the following report, in compliance with instructions of
                    Circular No. 4 from <abbr expan="Headquarters">H<hi rend="super"
                    >d</hi>Qrs</abbr> Sixth <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr> Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    June 1st 1866 directing renewal of application for information called for by
                    Circular No. 15 from <abbr expan="Current Series">C.S.</abbr> from <abbr
                        expan="Headquarters, Assistant Commissioner, State of Virginia">HdQrs. Asst.
                        Comr. State Va.</abbr> viz:</p>

                <p>Augusta County, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></p>

                <p>1 -- The <abbr expan="amount">Amt.</abbr> of <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> levy
                    required to be paid by each tithable person in the <abbr expan="County"
                    >Co.</abbr> is three (3) dollars each.</p>

                <p>2 -- The <abbr expan="amount">amt.</abbr> of poor levy in the <abbr
                        expan="County">Co.</abbr> is $15627.00 of which the sum of $6500 is for the
                    regular annual appropriation for the support of the poor and for the building of
                    additional houses for the accomodation of freedmen</p>

                <p>3 -- The class of colored males exempt from <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> and
                    poor tax consists of all those under sixteen years and <pb n="2"/>those who are
                    disabled from age and bodily infirmity</p>

                <p>4 -- There is no assessment on real estate to defray <abbr expan="County"
                    >Co.</abbr> and poor levy.</p>

                <p>5 -- There are 4259 white, and 950 colored tithables, making a total of 5209
                    tithables.</p>

                <p>Highland County, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></p>

                <p>1 -- The <abbr expan="amount">amt.</abbr> of <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> and
                    poor levy required to be paid by each tithable person is $3.25</p>

                <p>2 -- The <abbr expan="amount">Amt.</abbr> of poor levy is $795.22</p>

                <p>3 -- No colored males are exempt from <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> and poor
                    tax</p>

                <p>4 -- The <abbr expan="amount">amt.</abbr> laid on real estate per $100 valuation
                    to defray <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> levy and poor tax is 3 1/2 cents</p>

                <p>5 -- The comparative number of colored tithables with white tithables is 933
                    white to 50 colored tithables.</p>

                <p>The above reports are taken from reports of the County Clerks of the respective
                    Counties, for the year 1866.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Sir<lb/>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient"
                        >Obt.</abbr> Servant</salute>
                    <signed>Geo. T. Cook<lb/>1st <abbr expan="1st Lieutenant">1st Lt.</abbr> and
                            <abbr expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst. Supt.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
